errata "In Sec. 5.2 in the solution to the Exercise regarding the Red line, the solutions from 'c' onward are labeled improperly. 'c' should say ""Check students solution."" And the answers now labeled 'c' through 'h' should, instead, be labled 'd' through 'i'.
 {gc}"

errata ""In the homework for Sec. 3.4, the exercise about suicide rates is ambiguous. It says 'Do not include ""all others"" for parts f and g.' Therefore, I think the answer for f should be 23720/(29760 - 780).
 Also, think the answer for g should be 5010/(6020 - 100).
 {gc}""

errata "In section "9.5 Additional Information and Full Hypothesis Test Examples" of the online version of the book, there is a "Try It" problem about a right- tailed test. When you click the "Show Solution" button, an image appears that shows a left-tailed test. The normal distribution should be shaded to the right like the example above it. I am attaching a screenshot of the problem."
